node.text:
Acne Studios collaborates again with generative artist Robbie Barrat @robbie.exe, whose artificial intelligence-assisted figure studies feature as prints on a range of items from the Men's FW21 collection. 

Barrat took an unconventional approach to AI as an artistic tool by processing images taken from both classical figure paintings and Google Maps landscapes.

Discover the pieces in stores and on acnestudios.com

node.title: Robbie Barrat for Acne Studios Men's FW21

node.text:
A party celebrating #AcneStudios’ past, present and future.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Attended by over 2,000 guests in an empty office building in Frihamnen, the night was co-curated by long-term friends and collaborators of Acne Studios.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Throughout the space, installations by light and conceptual designer Tobias Rylander (@tobiasrylander) played with the ideas of reflection using alternative materials along with multiple video screens and projections. A laser show took place in the outdoor courtyard to give volume and depth to the empty space.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
As a nod to the past, one of the rooms was curated by Thomas Persson (@thomasperssonal), editor in chief of Acne Paper, and was inspired by the magazine first issue and its iconic red cover. The room saw a performance by Wild Daughter (@wild_daughter_), a project of visual artists and sound.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
The techno room, curated by Allegria Torassa (@allegriatorassa), featured mirror mosaic walls and beige carpeting in which DJ Pandora’s Jukebox (@pandorasjukebox) performed through the night.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Elsewhere at the party, DJs Romy Madley Croft (@romythexx) and Jerry Bouthier (@jerrybouthier) took turn on the turn tables and played on the 30-meters long mirror-covered mainstage. The evening ended with a live performance by Alex Knost (@knostthankyou) and his band, Tomorrows Tulips (@tomorrowstulips).
⁣⁣
A film by Sean Vegezzi (@seanvegezzi).

⁣
Season after season, stripes have been celebrated throughout Acne Studios’ collections as a playful accent to the brand. ⁣⁣⁣⁣For this collaboration, Swedish artist Jacob Dahlgren has been invited to create his own stripes which have been applied to our knitwear, scarves, beanies as well as an exclusive range of homeware pieces such as wallpaper, trays and wool blankets. ⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣
Acne Studios followed the artist to get a glimpse of his world and live a day of his stripes life, as documented daily on his Instagram (@Jacob_Dahlgren).⁣
⁣

node.text:
Acne Studios collaborates again with generative artist Robbie Barrat @robbie.exe, whose artificial intelligence-assisted figure studies feature as prints on a range of items from the Men's FW21 collection. 

Barrat took an unconventional approach to AI as an artistic tool by processing images taken from both classical figure paintings and Google Maps landscapes.

Discover the pieces in stores and on acnestudios.com
